{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":4,"markdown":"Since mid-2023, BCG vaccination volumes have averaged about 10 % below expected levels, reflecting a sustained but moderate shortfall in newborn immunization coverage that gradually stabilized within expected ranges by mid-2025.

Penta 1 and Penta 3 remained within expected levels, with monthly differences ranging from about –3 % to +3 %.
"},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":0.8,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"cf3b04ed-e85d-4eda-bdc5-6575b0240821","moduleId":"m003","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Slight disruptions for BCG, followed by recovery to expected levels in June 2025"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","titleTextRelFontSize":10,"subTitleText":"","subTitleTextRelFontSize":6,"presenterText":"","presenterTextRelFontSize":4,"dateText":"","dateTextRelFontSize":3,"logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","sectionTextRelFontSize":8,"smallerSectionText":"","smallerSectionTextRelFontSize":5},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":0.8,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":true,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"5a032a69-bab6-410e-a906-77e13ace3724","moduleId":"m003","isDefault":false,"selectedReplicantValue":""}}],[{"type":"text","markdown":"For neonatal deaths (<1 month), numbers rose from 740 in Q1 2020 to a peak of 1,005 in Q2 2022, followed by a consistent downward trend through 2024 and 2025, reaching around 593 in Q3 2025 — a decline of roughly 40% from the peak.

Similarly, post-neonatal deaths (1–11 months) increased from 315 in Q1 2020 to above 500 in 2022, then dropped steadily to about 247 in Q2 2025, before a slight uptick to 315 in Q3 2025.

Together, these trends suggest that infant deaths declined notably from 2023 onward, coinciding with a general reduction in maternal and child health service volumes observed during the same period. While this could reflect genuine improvement in outcomes, it is also possible that data underreporting or reduced facility-based births contributed to the decline. The stabilization seen in mid-2025 may indicate a slow recovery in reporting or service coverage.","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"success","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":false,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false}]]}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","titleTextRelFontSize":10,"subTitleText":"","subTitleTextRelFontSize":6,"presenterText":"","presenterTextRelFontSize":4,"dateText":"","dateTextRelFontSize":3,"logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","sectionTextRelFontSize":8,"smallerSectionText":"","smallerSectionTextRelFontSize":5},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":0.7,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"7cda3433-4be7-4d56-83de-3734609d0379","moduleId":"m003","isDefault":false,"selectedReplicantValue":""}}],[{"type":"text","markdown":"Across all six selected regions, institutional delivery service utilization shows a similar pattern of steady performance from 2020 through 2023, followed by a noticeable decline in 2024 and a sharper drop in 2025.

Central and Northern Regions maintained the highest service volumes through 2022–2023, peaking around 75,000–80,000 deliveries before falling by roughly 15–25% in 2025.

Upper East, Upper West, North East, and Volta Regions also show gradual growth up to 2022–2023, followed by contractions in 2024–2025, with the most pronounced declines occurring in Upper East and Volta (around 20–30% lower than previous peaks).","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"success","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":false,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false}]]}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","titleTextRelFontSize":10,"subTitleText":"","subTitleTextRelFontSize":6,"presenterText":"","presenterTextRelFontSize":4,"dateText":"","dateTextRelFontSize":3,"logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","sectionTextRelFontSize":8,"smallerSectionText":"","smallerSectionTextRelFontSize":5},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","markdown":"PNC utilization increased steadily from 737,878 in 2020 to a peak of 819,225 in 2022, indicating improvements in service uptake during that period. The trend then stabilized around 812,965 in 2023, suggesting sustained performance before a moderate drop to 770,893 in 2024.

By 2025, however, service utilization declined sharply to 599,783, marking a substantial reduction compared to previous years. This represents a drop of roughly 25% relative to 2024 levels.

Overall, the data reflect strong progress in PNC coverage up to 2023, followed by a significant decline in 2025, which could indicate reduced service availability, reporting completeness, or changes in health-seeking behavior during that period.","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"success","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":false,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false}],[{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":true,"hideFigureSubCaption":true,"hideFigureFootnote":true,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"a0dbe5b3-dcff-4621-9c8e-7e12bb61735d","moduleId":"m003","isDefault":false,"selectedReplicantValue":""}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"PNC Service Utilization, Jan 2020 - Sept 2025"}}

