{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":4,"markdown":"ANC1 volumes through 2025 remained slightly above expected levels (~7 %), with volumes returning to expected in June.

ANC4 stayed close to trend in 2025, averaging ~70 000 monthly vs. ~68 600 expected (~2 % higher), with service volumes returning to expected in June.

Both indicators follow expected trajectories, though ANC1 shows modest gains, while fewer women complete ANC4, pointing to persistent continuity gaps in antenatal care."},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"b59de1be-c6c8-4559-90a3-a5bc86b8bf67","moduleId":"m003","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"ANC1 shows slight surpluses in 2025, while ANC4 stays near trend, but continuity gap remains"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","titleTextRelFontSize":10,"subTitleText":"","subTitleTextRelFontSize":6,"presenterText":"","presenterTextRelFontSize":4,"dateText":"","dateTextRelFontSize":3,"logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","sectionTextRelFontSize":8,"smallerSectionText":"","smallerSectionTextRelFontSize":5},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","markdown":"PNC utilization increased steadily from 737,878 in 2020 to a peak of 819,225 in 2022, indicating improvements in service uptake during that period. The trend then stabilized around 812,965 in 2023, suggesting sustained performance before a moderate drop to 770,893 in 2024.

By 2025, however, service utilization declined sharply to 599,783, marking a substantial reduction compared to previous years. This represents a drop of roughly 25% relative to 2024 levels.

Overall, the data reflect strong progress in PNC coverage up to 2023, followed by a significant decline in 2025, which could indicate reduced service availability, reporting completeness, or changes in health-seeking behavior during that period.","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"success","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":false,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false}],[{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":true,"hideFigureSubCaption":true,"hideFigureFootnote":true,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"a0dbe5b3-dcff-4621-9c8e-7e12bb61735d","moduleId":"m003","isDefault":false,"selectedReplicantValue":""}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"PNC Service Utilization, Jan 2020 - Sept 2025"}}

